Description: Python bindings for GNOME2
DescDetail: <<
gnome-python2 provides bindings for the GNOME2 libraries to use the
Python programming language.

gnome-python2-extras contains less-often-used GNOME2 bindings that
were off-loaded from gnome-python2 starting with version 2.9.1.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
  'make check' requires active x11 display.

  Disable gdl bindings because our gdl is not shared and has no .pc file.

  Disable gda bindings because our lib is too old.

  configure autodetects and builds bindinds for whatever support libs
  are found. We want to make sure we get things built as expected, so
  patch configure to crash unless desired bindings would be built.
<<
DescPort: <<
  Fix __PyGObject_API symbol scoping, inclusion in *.o. See:
  http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=345388

  Fix passing of pygtk codegen paths. See:
  http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=345390
